CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1946, pg. 29 reads: "Lawn Luncheon - Mrs. Jane Williams of Webster Avenue recently gave a delightful lawn luncheon in honor of Mr. and Mrs. C.J. Ford of Roxboro, N.C. The hostess is the niece of the Fords, who are widely-known in social and civic circles throughout their native state.  A number of out-of-towners attended the affair. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, men, boys, and girls, including girl wearing striped top under jumper, and holding ball, gathered in yard of Jane Williams, Webster Avenue, Hill District
